com.bmd.android.collection.iterator

Interface ElementSparseIterable<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<E>, SparseIterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BooleanSparseIterable, IntSparseIterable, LongSparseIterable

    public interface ElementSparseIterable<E>
extends SparseIterable<E>
    This interface extends the SparseIterable one by adding specific methods handling serialization of the elements to lists and arrays.

    Created by davide on 3/10/14.

      • fill

        <T> ElementSparseIterable<E> fill(T[] array)
        Fills the specified array with the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order, starting from the index 0 of the array.

        Note that, if the elements returned by the iterable cannot be cast to the array elements type, a ClassCastException will be thrown.

        Note also that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the array elements type.
        Parameters:
        array - the array to fill.
        Returns:
        this iterable.

      • fill

        <T> ElementSparseIterable<E> fill(T[] array,
                                int offset)
        Fills the specified array with the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order, starting from the specified offset inside the array.

        Note that, if the elements returned by the iterable cannot be cast to the array elements type, a ClassCastException will be thrown.

        Note also that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:

        Parameters:

        offset - the offset from which to start filling the array.
